{
  "doc_id": "56967",
  "text": "The fact that algorithms based on single predictors, such as d.b.h. or AS d.b.h. , systematically underestimate FB in younger (our data) or older stands [CITATION_1] suggests that the departure of the relationship between d.b.h. or AS and FB is due to variations in canopy characteristics, such as crown condition, crown depth and degree of self-shading. As expected, the inclusion of canopy openness and crown depth improved estimates of FB [CITATION_2] and overcame the bias for underestimating this value in younger (this study) and older stands [CITATION_3] , most likely by accounting for differences associated with management practices (timing of thinning cycles, etc.).",
